November 5, 2025
ME and LE Flux landscape scan
--> According to Rob Fine, flux slack channel, MINERvA chat: Jaewon was working with 1000 LE flux
    universes for the nu-e constraint analysis, looks like he had flux weights for all those
    universes baked directly into his analysis ntuples
    --> Rob thinks Jaewon's work predated a standard tool to pull the flux weights at analysis time
        --> It's possible that when FRW was developed his code was used, but for whatever reason the norm of using
            only 100 flux universes was established?
    --> Don't know if we have the same 1000 universes for ME and for LE (Rob doesn't remember investigating, 
    though the question came up when he was writing his thesis)
--> Laura email, October 27, 2025: says PPFX makes central value weights for each event during anatuple 
    production
    --> 1000 hadron production universe weights are also made using PPFX
    --> 1000 (?) flux focusing weights also made
    --> After anatuple production, a script is run that constructs a central value flux for each neutrino flavour and
        configuration + 1000 combined uncertainty universes (obtained by multipying the hadron production and focusing wgts)
    --> NuE scattering + IMD weights constructed for each of the combined flux universes (Laura not sure if this is anatuple 
        production or flux histograms)
    --> Another script reorders the universes from 2 steps ago according to the size of the NuE scattering + IMD wgts
    --> The reordered flux MnvH1Ds + reordered NuE scattering weights are used by FluxReweighter to provide CV and flux 
        universe weights to analyzers
        --> At this point, weights are only a function of neutrino energy, not the entire neutrino flux ancestry

